How to use CIO_LED_FLASH:

CIO_LED_FLASH  that makeS the selected led flash continuously
You can specify the LED to be used, as well as the on and off times, as parameters
NOTE:Interrupting the program will cause the LED to stop flashing

sudo bash <directory>/CIO_LED_FLASH <LED_COLOR> <t_on> <tt_off>

CIO_LED_FLASH have 3 parameter
LED_COLOR	# LEDnumber + LEDcolor,LEDnumber=LED1 color=green ,It can be like "LED1_GREEN",must be all uppercase type
t_on		# off time in second,  float values possible,minimum 0.05
t_off		# on time in second,  float values possible,minimum 0.05

----------------------------------------------
---LED_COLOR-------LED NUMBER---------COLOR---
----------------------------------------------
---LED1_GREEN---------LED1------------GREEN---
---LED1_RED-----------LED1------------RED-----
---LED1_ORANGE--------LED1------------ORANGE--
----------------------------------------------
---LED2_GREEN---------LED2------------GREEN---
---LED2_RED-----------LED2------------RED-----
---LED2_ORANGE--------LED2------------ORANGE--
----------------------------------------------
---LED3_GREEN---------LED3------------GREEN---
---LED3_RED-----------LED3------------RED-----
---LED3_ORANGE--------LED3------------ORANGE--

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Controlling LEDs as the root user:

sudo ./CIO_LED_FLASH -m LED1_RED 0.5 0.5
sudo ./CIO_LED_FLASH -m LED3_ORANGE 1.5 1.5

LEDs can be modified on the fly
1.stop LED1 flash
LED1 0 0

2.stop all led
LED 0 0 

3.Use other LEDs
LED3_GREEN 1 1

 
Ctrl + c ,stop CIO_LED_FLASH

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
sample code:

#control LED1 flash orange color ,time_on 1 sec, time off 1 sec

#include <libF75113.h>
#include <SMBus/SMBus.h>
typedef struct
{
	double t_off;
	double t_on;
	char *color;
	bool flash;
}LED_CONFIG;

LED_CONFIG LED_C;
if(!SMBus_Install())
	{
		printf("SMBus_Install fail \n");
		exit(0);
	}
if(!F75113_Init())
	{
		printf("F75113 init fail \n");
		exit(0);
	}
bzero(&LED_C,sizeof(LED_C));
LED_C.t_on=1;
LED_C.t_off=1;
LED_C.color="LED1_ORANGE";

Led1_Control(LED_CONFIG LED_C);


